<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Luckify Me — Quantitative Model Update 2026</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Serif+Display:ital@0;1&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

  :root {
    --black:      #0C0C0C;
    --orange:     #E07840;
    --orange-dim: #C4693A;
    --cream:      #F7F4EF;
    --warm-white: #FDFCFA;
    --gray-1:     #1C1C1C;
    --gray-2:     #3A3834;
    --gray-3:     #7A7670;
    --gray-4:     #B8B4AE;
    --gray-5:     #E2DED8;
    --green:      #2D6A4A;
    --gold:       #A07828;
  }

  html { background: var(--black); }

  body {
    font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
    background: var(--warm-white);
    color: var(--gray-1);
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }

  /* ── TOP ACCENT ── */
  .top-bar {
    height: 3px;
    background: var(--orange);
  }

  /* ── HEADER ── */
  header {
    padding: 52px 56px 44px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
    align-items: end;
    gap: 24px;
  }

  .brand-label {
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    color: var(--orange);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  h1 {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    font-size: 38px;
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: var(--black);
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  h1 em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--orange-dim);
  }

  .header-meta {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--gray-3);
    margin-top: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  .header-right {
    text-align: right;
  }

  .edition-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gray-3);
    border: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
    padding: 6px 12px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  /* ── STAT ROW ── */
  .stats {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
  }

  .stat {
    padding: 28px 28px 24px;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
    position: relative;
  }
  .stat:last-child { border-right: none; }

  .stat-num {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    font-size: 36px;
    color: var(--orange);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gray-3);
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  .stat-sub {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--gray-4);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  /* ── MAIN CONTENT ── */
  main {
    padding: 0 56px;
  }

  /* ── SECTION ── */
  .section {
    padding: 40px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
  }
  .section:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .section-label {
    font-size: 9.5px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--orange);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .section-label::after {
    content: '';
    display: block;
    height: 1px;
    flex: 1;
    background: var(--gray-5);
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--black);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--gray-2);
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    max-width: 680px;
  }
  p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  p strong { color: var(--black); font-weight: 600; }

  /* ── CALLOUT ── */
  .callout {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--orange);
    background: #FEF6EF;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    margin: 18px 0;
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
  }
  .callout-label {
    font-size: 9px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--orange);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .callout p {
    font-size: 13.5px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--gray-1);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: none;
  }

  /* ── TWO COL ── */
  .two-col {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-top: 18px;
  }

  /* ── SIGNAL PILLS ── */
  .signals {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-top: 18px;
  }

  .signal-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 110px 120px 1fr;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 14px;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    background: var(--cream);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .signal-name {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--black);
  }

  .signal-badge {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 5px;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 3px 9px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .badge-green  { background: #E8F5EE; color: var(--green); }
  .badge-red    { background: #FAECEC; color: #B22222; }
  .badge-gold   { background: #FBF4E4; color: var(--gold); }
  .badge-gray   { background: var(--gray-5); color: var(--gray-3); }
  .badge-orange { background: #FEF0E6; color: var(--orange-dim); }

  .signal-desc {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--gray-3);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* ── FLAGSHIP BOX ── */
  .flagship {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
    gap: 0;
    margin-top: 18px;
    border: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .flag-cell {
    padding: 24px 20px;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .flag-cell.before { background: var(--cream); }
  .flag-cell.arrow  { background: var(--warm-white); display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border-left: 1px solid var(--gray-5); border-right: 1px solid var(--gray-5); }
  .flag-cell.after  { background: #FEF6EF; }

  .flag-tag {
    font-size: 9px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .flag-cell.before .flag-tag { color: var(--gray-3); }
  .flag-cell.after  .flag-tag { color: var(--orange); }

  .flag-num {
    font-family: 'DM Serif Display', serif;
    font-size: 44px;
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .flag-cell.before .flag-num { color: var(--black); }
  .flag-cell.after  .flag-num { color: var(--orange); }

  .flag-sub {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--gray-3);
  }
  .flag-cell.after .flag-sub { color: #C4793A; }

  .arrow-icon {
    font-size: 22px;
    color: var(--orange);
  }

  /* ── MARKET TABLE ── */
  .market-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin-top: 18px;
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  .market-table th {
    text-align: left;
    font-size: 9.5px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gray-3);
    padding: 10px 14px;
    background: var(--cream);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
  }

  .market-table td {
    padding: 12px 14px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
    vertical-align: top;
    color: var(--gray-2);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .market-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .market-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--cream); }

  .market-table td:first-child {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--black);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .status-pill {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 9.5px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 3px 9px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  /* ── ROADMAP ── */
  .roadmap {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    margin-top: 18px;
    border: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .road-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 36px 1fr auto;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
  }
  .road-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .road-num {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    align-self: stretch;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: white;
    width: 36px;
  }
  .road-num.done   { background: var(--green); }
  .road-num.active { background: var(--orange); }
  .road-num.next   { background: var(--gold); }
  .road-num.future { background: var(--gray-4); }

  .road-content {
    padding: 13px 16px;
  }
  .road-title {
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--black);
    margin-bottom: 2px;
  }
  .road-desc {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--gray-3);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .road-status {
    padding: 0 16px;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .road-status.done   { color: var(--green); }
  .road-status.active { color: var(--orange); }
  .road-status.next   { color: var(--gold); }
  .road-status.future { color: var(--gray-4); }

  /* ── FOOTER ── */
  footer {
    padding: 28px 56px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }

  .footer-brand {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gray-4);
  }

  .footer-note {
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--gray-4);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── PRINT / SHARE ── */
  @media print {
    body { max-width: 100%; }
    .top-bar { print-color-adjust: exact; -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; }
    .stat-num, .flag-num { print-color-adjust: exact; -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; }
  }

  /* ── MOBILE ── */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    header {
      padding: 32px 24px 28px;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 16px;
    }

    h1 { font-size: 28px; }

    .header-right { text-align: left; }

    .stats {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
    .stat {
      padding: 20px 18px 16px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
    }
    .stat:nth-child(2) { border-right: none; }
    .stat:nth-child(3) { border-bottom: none; }
    .stat:nth-child(4) { border-right: none; border-bottom: none; }
    .stat-num { font-size: 28px; }

    main { padding: 0 24px; }

    .section { padding: 28px 0; }

    h2 { font-size: 19px; }

    p { font-size: 13.5px; max-width: 100%; }

    .flagship {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      grid-template-rows: auto auto auto;
    }
    .flag-cell.arrow {
      border-left: none;
      border-right: none;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
      padding: 10px;
    }
    .arrow-icon {
      transform: rotate(90deg);
      display: inline-block;
    }
    .flag-num { font-size: 36px; }

    .signal-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 6px;
      padding: 14px 14px;
    }
    .signal-name { font-size: 13px; }
    .signal-desc { font-size: 12px; }

    .market-table thead { display: none; }
    .market-table, .market-table tbody,
    .market-table tr, .market-table td { display: block; width: 100%; }
    .market-table tr {
      margin-bottom: 12px;
      border: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
      border-radius: 4px;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .market-table tr:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .market-table td {
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-5);
      padding: 10px 14px;
      font-size: 13px;
    }
    .market-table td:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .market-table td:first-child {
      background: var(--cream);
      font-size: 13px;
    }

    .road-row { grid-template-columns: 36px 1fr; }
    .road-status { display: none; }
    .road-title { font-size: 13px; }
    .road-desc { font-size: 11.5px; }

    footer {
      padding: 24px 24px;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 6px;
    }
  }

  /* ── ANIMATIONS ── */
  @keyframes fadeUp {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(14px); }
    to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  .stats, header, .section {
    animation: fadeUp 0.5s ease both;
  }
  header        { animation-delay: 0.05s; }
  .stats        { animation-delay: 0.15s; }
  .section:nth-child(1) { animation-delay: 0.2s; }
  .section:nth-child(2) { animation-delay: 0.25s; }
  .section:nth-child(3) { animation-delay: 0.3s; }
  .section:nth-child(4) { animation-delay: 0.35s; }
  .section:nth-child(5) { animation-delay: 0.4s; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="top-bar"></div>

<!-- HEADER -->
<header>
  <div>
    <div class="brand-label">Luckify Me</div>
    <h1>Quantitative Model<br><em>Update — 2026</em></h1>
    <div class="header-meta">March 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp; PGA Tour Golf &nbsp;·&nbsp; Findings & Strategy Summary</div>
  </div>
  <div class="header-right">
    <div class="edition-tag">Confidential &nbsp;·&nbsp; Q1 2026</div>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- STATS -->
<div class="stats">
  <div class="stat">
    <div class="stat-label">Signal Accuracy</div>
    <div class="stat-num">64.9%</div>
    <div class="stat-sub">correct direction on unseen data</div>
  </div>
  <div class="stat">
    <div class="stat-label">Confidence Level</div>
    <div class="stat-num">99.7%</div>
    <div class="stat-sub">probability signals are not random</div>
  </div>
  <div class="stat">
    <div class="stat-label">Validated Signals</div>
    <div class="stat-num">254</div>
    <div class="stat-sub">high-confidence edges after correction</div>
  </div>
  <div class="stat">
    <div class="stat-label">Combinations Tested</div>
    <div class="stat-num">7,304</div>
    <div class="stat-sub">variable combinations rigorously tested</div>
  </div>
</div>

<main>

  <!-- 01 ORIGIN -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">01 &nbsp; Where We Started</div>
    <h2>An Honest Starting Point</h2>
    <p>When we began testing in golf, we broke even. That is worth saying plainly — and it is also the point. We were in the variable discovery phase, building data infrastructure before deploying capital. Most operations skip this step. We did not.</p>
    <p>That discipline is what makes everything that followed meaningful. <strong>That period is now behind us.</strong></p>
  </div>

  <!-- 02 VALIDATION -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">02 &nbsp; Validation Results</div>
    <h2>What the Data Confirmed</h2>
    <p>Every signal was tested against 2025–2026 data the model had never seen — the gold standard in quantitative research. The question is not whether patterns exist in historical data. The question is whether they survive contact with the future.</p>

    <div class="callout">
      <div class="callout-label">Key Finding</div>
      <p>64.9% of our signals predicted the correct outcome on unseen data. The probability of that happening by random chance is <strong>0.3%</strong> — meaning there is a <strong>99.7% statistical probability</strong> these edges are real. In quantitative finance, retaining 30–40% of signal magnitude on new data is considered a success. Our best cluster retained <strong>72%</strong>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="flagship">
      <div class="flag-cell before">
        <div class="flag-tag">Training Data</div>
        <div class="flag-num">−2.06</div>
        <div class="flag-sub">stroke edge</div>
      </div>
      <div class="flag-cell arrow">
        <div class="arrow-icon">→</div>
      </div>
      <div class="flag-cell after">
        <div class="flag-tag">Out-of-Sample · 2025–26</div>
        <div class="flag-num">−2.94</div>
        <div class="flag-sub">signal got stronger</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 03 SIGNALS -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">03 &nbsp; Signal Structure</div>
    <h2>What the Model Identified</h2>
    <p>One proprietary variable category emerged as the dominant structural predictor — present in the top 7 most consistent signal types across the entire dataset. It is invisible to every mainstream betting market in existence. The market does not price it.</p>
    <p>Within it, five distinct phases were identified:</p>

    <div class="signals">
      <div class="signal-row">
        <div class="signal-name">Green Phase</div>
        <div><span class="signal-badge badge-green">Consistent Positive</span></div>
        <div class="signal-desc">Most broadly applicable signal. Near-zero probability of randomness. n=462 in peak combination.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="signal-row">
        <div class="signal-name">Amplifier Phase</div>
        <div><span class="signal-badge badge-gold">Round-Dependent</span></div>
        <div class="signal-desc">Strongest positive in Round 4. Reverses sharply in Round 1. Direction is context-driven — must be used with round data.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="signal-row">
        <div class="signal-name">Red Phase</div>
        <div><span class="signal-badge badge-red">Reliable Negative</span></div>
        <div class="signal-desc">67% of the tour field underperforms in Round 2. Player-agnostic. Confirmed out-of-sample.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="signal-row">
        <div class="signal-name">Conditional Phase</div>
        <div><span class="signal-badge badge-orange">Cycle-Dependent</span></div>
        <div class="signal-desc">Positive in the first half of the broader cycle. Consistently negative in the second. n=546.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="signal-row">
        <div class="signal-name">Noise Phase</div>
        <div><span class="signal-badge badge-gray">Removed</span></div>
        <div class="signal-desc">Failed to replicate on new data. Removed from model entirely.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 04 MARKETS -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">04 &nbsp; Market Strategy</div>
    <h2>Finding the Most Exploitable Markets</h2>
    <p>Validated signals only generate returns in the right markets. We have been systematically testing and isolating which formats our edge is largest in — and where the market's pricing inefficiencies are most concentrated.</p>

    <table class="market-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Market</th>
          <th>Why We're Here</th>
          <th>Status</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>2-Ball Matchups</td>
          <td>Highest edge concentration. Head-to-head format removes field noise. Our variables are entirely absent from market pricing.</td>
          <td><span class="status-pill" style="background:#FEF0E6;color:#C4693A;">Active Testing</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>3-Ball Matchups</td>
          <td>Three-way format isolates round-specific performance cleanly. Smaller fields amplify relative edge.</td>
          <td><span class="status-pill" style="background:#FEF0E6;color:#C4693A;">Active Testing</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Round Scoring Totals</td>
          <td>Direct application of round-condition signals. R1 and R4 Moderate findings map precisely to this format.</td>
          <td><span class="status-pill" style="background:#FBF4E4;color:#A07828;">Evaluating</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Outright Winner</td>
          <td>Largest liquidity but most efficient pricing. Player-segmentation work will target specific players here in a future phase.</td>
          <td><span class="status-pill" style="background:var(--gray-5);color:var(--gray-3);">Future Phase</span></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- 05 ROADMAP -->
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">05 &nbsp; Roadmap</div>
    <h2>Where We Are. Where We're Going.</h2>
    <p>The foundation is built. Deployment is the next phase.</p>

    <div class="roadmap">
      <div class="road-row">
        <div class="road-num done">1</div>
        <div class="road-content">
          <div class="road-title">Variable Framework</div>
          <div class="road-desc">Dominant predictor identified across 7,304 combinations. Noise variables isolated and removed.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="road-status done">Complete</div>
      </div>
      <div class="road-row">
        <div class="road-num done">2</div>
        <div class="road-content">
          <div class="road-title">Out-of-Sample Validation</div>
          <div class="road-desc">99.7% confidence on unseen 2025–2026 data. Flagship signal strengthened on new data.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="road-status done">Complete</div>
      </div>
      <div class="road-row">
        <div class="road-num done">3</div>
        <div class="road-content">
          <div class="road-title">Signal Hierarchy Mapped</div>
          <div class="road-desc">All five phases documented with round and cycle dependencies defined.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="road-status done">Complete</div>
      </div>
      <div class="road-row">
        <div class="road-num active">4</div>
